cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SI, cs.DL. 

This paper investigates the lag in vulnerability updates in third-party libraries, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) concern. The focus is on security fixes, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The study is conducted on the npm JavaScript ecosystem, which is a programming languages (cs.PL) topic. The paper also uses both qualitative and quantitative approaches, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.DL).
